  "text": "The recovery of sparse objects (e.g., signals, images) or representations u ∈ R N using a few basis vectors from few and possibly inaccurate data d ∈ R M is an extremely lively area of research in linear inverse problems and in compressed sensing [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The most natural measure of sparsity is the counting function . 0 , called usually the 0 -norm",
